tournament.name: Coupe de France  - Team Trio Unified

decks.notes: The deck focuses on ramping up mana quickly with cards like Exploration, Burgeoning, and Azusa, Lost but Seeking to get out big threats like Primeval Titan and Emrakul, the Promised End. It also utilizes land destruction like Ghost Quarter and Dust Bowl to disrupt opponents' mana bases. Crucible of Worlds and Ramunap Excavator allow for constant land recursion, while cards like Life from the Loam and Sylvan Library provide card advantage. Control elements like All Is Dust and Ugin, the Spirit Dragon help deal with threats on the board. The deck aims to overwhelm opponents with powerful creatures and disruptive land strategies, ultimately out-valuing and outpacing them to secure victory.

The key focus of this deck is to maintain control over the game through a variety of counterspells, removal spells, and disruptive creatures. Glarb, Calamity's Augur serves as the commander, providing card advantage and a threatening presence on the battlefield. The deck includes a wide range of mana fixing lands to ensure consistent access to all colors of mana. The inclusion of powerful spells like Force of Will, Demonic Tutor, and Toxic Deluge allows for versatile answers to opposing threats. By using a combination of permission spells and disruptive creatures like Baleful Strix and Murktide Regent, the deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan while setting up a win condition through card advantage and efficient removal.

The deck focuses on utilizing the two Partner commanders, Dargo and Yoshimaru, to create a fast and aggressive strategy. The deck includes a mix of powerful creatures, efficient removal spells, and impactful artifacts to quickly build a threatening board presence. Cards like Abstergo Entertainment, Embercleave, and Skullclamp help push damage through and generate card advantage. The mana base is optimized for consistency and speed, with a mix of dual lands and utility lands like Arid Mesa and Sunbaked Canyon. Overall, the deck aims to overwhelm opponents with its aggressive creatures and removal spells, while also having the flexibility to adapt to various board states.

This deck focuses on fast and aggressive play with a combination of black and red cards. The commanders, Rograkh and Tevesh Szat, provide a strong presence on the battlefield and enable quick and efficient plays. The deck includes a variety of rituals and fast mana sources to accelerate mana production and cast powerful spells early in the game. It also contains a mix of disruptive spells like Thoughtseize and Cabal Therapy to disrupt the opponent's strategy. Additionally, the deck features cards like Tendrils of Agony and Underworld Breach for powerful combo potential and the ability to finish off the opponent quickly. Overall, this deck aims to apply pressure and outpace the opponent to secure a victory.

This deck focuses on utilizing Teferi, Temporal Archmage's ability to untap four permanents to generate infinite mana, draw through the entire library, and eventually win the game through a combo finish. The deck contains multiple ways to control the game, with numerous counterspells and bounce spells to disrupt opponents' strategies while setting up its own win conditions. The inclusion of High Tide and other mana ramp cards helps to generate the necessary mana to fuel the combo. By efficiently controlling the board and consistently drawing through the deck, this deck aims to assemble its combo pieces and win the game through a powerful combo finish using Teferi's untap ability.

The deck focuses on utilizing aggressive creatures and powerful white removal spells to control the board and quickly defeat the opponent. With a mix of efficient creatures like Isamaru, Hound of Konda and Thalia, Guardian of Thraben, alongside disruptive cards such as Thalia, Heretic Cathar and Giver of Runes, the deck aims to apply early pressure while also disrupting the opponent's game plan. In addition, the deck includes powerful removal spells like Swords to Plowshares and Skyclave Apparition to deal with threats efficiently. The inclusion of equipment like Skullclamp and Shadowspear helps to further enhance the deck's aggression and effectiveness in combat, making it a formidable force in the Duel Commander format.

The main idea of this deck is to utilize Acererak the Archlich as the commander to assemble powerful combos and control the game. This deck focuses on disrupting opponents with cards like Duress, Thoughtseize, and Inquisition of Kozilek while ramping up mana with cards like Cabal Coffers and Dark Ritual. By using various tutors like Demonic Tutor and Grim Tutor, the deck aims to find key combo pieces such as Necropotence and Yawgmoth's Will to generate massive card advantage and graveyard recursion. The deck also includes powerful board wipes like Damnation and Toxic Deluge to maintain control over the battlefield. Overall, the goal is to outvalue opponents through efficient resource management and explosive combo potential.

The main focus of this deck is to apply early pressure on the opponent with aggressive creatures and efficient removal spells. By utilizing cards like Lightning Bolt, Swords to Plowshares, and Bonecrusher Giant, the deck aims to control the board and keep the opponent on the back foot. The inclusion of powerful planeswalkers like Teferi, Time Raveler and Ajani, Nacatl Pariah provides additional support and disruption to maintain dominance. The deck also features a mix of countermagic and card draw to ensure consistency and adaptability in different matchups. Overall, the strategy revolves around establishing a strong board presence quickly and maintaining control throughout the game to secure victory.

The deck focuses on utilizing Malcolm, Alluring Scoundrel as the commander to create aggressive and disruptive plays. It includes a wide range of counterspells and interactive spells to control the game and protect your threats. The strategy revolves around tempo plays, leveraging card advantage and efficient mana usage to outmaneuver opponents. By disrupting their plans and maintaining pressure with evasive creatures like True-Name Nemesis and Murktide Regent, the deck aims to close out the game quickly. Additionally, it includes various ways to manipulate the top of the library and draw cards to ensure consistency in finding the right answers at the right time.

This deck is focused on aggressive gameplay with a strong emphasis on controlling the opponent's board state. By utilizing a variety of disruptive creatures and support spells, the deck aims to maintain pressure on the opponent while preventing them from establishing a strong presence on the battlefield. Phelia, Exuberant Shepherd serves as the commander, providing a consistent source of aggressive threats. With cards like Thalia, Guardian of Thraben, Swords to Plowshares, and Stoneforge Mystic, the deck is designed to disrupt the opponent's strategy while maintaining a steady flow of threats. By maintaining a balance between aggression and disruption, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent and secure victory through efficient and strategic play.

The deck focuses on utilizing the sacrifice and token generation abilities of Slimefoot and Squee to create a continuous stream of value and pressure on the opponent. It includes a mix of versatile removal spells, mana acceleration, and powerful creatures to swiftly overwhelm the opponent. The deck aims to control the board with disruption spells like Thoughtseize and Abrupt Decay while building its own army of tokens with cards like Blood Artist and Tarmogoyf. By sacrificing creatures and utilizing effects like Goblin Bombardment, the deck can close out games quickly and efficiently. Overall, the key concept of this deck is to create a proactive and aggressive game plan that leverages the synergy between Slimefoot and Squee to outvalue and outpace the opponent.

The main focus of this deck is to efficiently combo off and win the game using Acererak the Archlich as the commander. The deck includes various cards that disrupt opponents' hands and board states, such as Thoughtseize, Duress, and Inquisition of Kozilek. It also contains powerful tutoring cards like Demonic Tutor and Grim Tutor to find key combo pieces quickly. The deck aims to generate a large amount of mana with cards like Cabal Coffers and Dark Ritual, while also using spells like Tendrils of Agony and Consuming Corruption to drain opponents' life totals. Overall, the strategy revolves around assembling the combo pieces needed to win the game through efficient and powerful synergies.

This deck aims to overwhelm opponents with aggressive creatures and pump spells, utilizing the partner commanders to create a powerful and synergistic strategy. By combining the Sword Coast Sailor's ability to draw extra cards with Wilson, Refined Grizzly's ability to pump up creatures, the deck aims to quickly build a board presence and push for fast wins. With a mix of efficient counter spells and protection spells, the deck can protect its threats and disrupt opponents' game plans. The inclusion of powerful cards like True-Name Nemesis and Oko, Thief of Crowns further adds to the deck's aggressiveness and versatility. Overall, the deck focuses on applying early pressure and maintaining tempo to secure victories in the 1 vs 1 format.

This deck focuses on a powerful aggressive strategy using the Partner commanders Dargo, the Shipwrecker and Yoshimaru, Ever Faithful in a Duel Commander format. The deck aims to quickly establish a board presence and deal damage to the opponent efficiently. It includes a mix of aggressive creatures like Kari Zev, Skyship Raider and Adeline, Resplendent Cathar, along with burn spells like Lightning Bolt and Chain Lightning to control the board and finish off the opponent. Additionally, the deck includes powerful equipment such as Embercleave and Skullclamp to enhance the combat abilities of its creatures. The mana base is optimized to support the aggressive game plan with plenty of dual lands and fetch lands to ensure consistent mana production.
